Finch County was named in honour of the Surveyor Heneage Finch.

Finch County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It is bounded by the Narran River in the west, the Barwon River to the south and east, and the Queensland border to the north. It includes Lightning Ridge .
